Biography

Sarah Ann was born 11 March 1817 in Middlesex Township, Butler County, Pennsylvania. She was the oldest daughter of William Kennedy and Mary McDonald.

She married Windle Hickey and had seven known children.

On 24 November 1848, Sarah Ann Hickey was named as an heir of William Kennedy when William's siblings signed a quit claim to their brother Joseph Kennedy of Middlesex Township, Butler County, Pennsylvania for 250 acres in the same township, recorded 24 February 1874. The deed names William's siblings George Kennedy, Elizabeth Critchlow (and husband Alexander), Isabel Lee (and husband Thomas), James Kennedy, and names William's children as Sarah Ann Hickey (and husband Windle), Henry Kennedy, Isabella Kennedy, Alexander Kennedy, Benedict Kennedy, and Rebecca Kennedy.[1]

On 25 January 1850, Sarah Ann was named as an heir when her father's estate in MIddlesex Township, Butler County, Pennsylvania, was settled by brother Henry Kennedy and wife Sarah Ann of Meigs County, Ohio, recorded 11 February 1850. The deed names William Kennedy's children as Sarah Ann Hickey, Isabel Kennedy, Henry M Kennedy, Alexander Kennedy, and Benedict Kennedy.[2]

On 1 February 1850, Sarah Ann was named as an heir when she and her siblings sold the land that was part her father's estate in Middlesex Township, Butler County, Pennsylvania, to Thomas Moore, recorded 16 January 1851. The deed names her father's children as Sarah Ann Hickey, Isabel Kennedy, Henry M Kennedy, Alexander Kennedy, and Benedict Kennedy.[3]

She died on 19 March 1891 in Middlesex Township, Butler County, Pennsylvania. She was buried at Middlesex Methodist Cemetery in Middlesex Township, Butler County, Pennsylvania.[4]
